unchanged. In all, 1.63 billion shares changed hands on a market
turnover of NT$112.45 billion (US$3.93 billion).
</P>
<P>
Among the eight stock categories, paper-making and construction
issues declined 1.2 percent, respectively, while cement shares dipped
0.3 percent and textiles lost 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, foodstuff stocks increased 0.7 percent, banking issues
grew 0.4 percent and plastic and chemical stocks rose 0.2 percent.
</P>
