congress from the balcony of the meeting hall. But the elections were
held behind closed doors just as at the 14th Party Congress,
reporters were not allowed to witness the actual process of electing
members of the Central Committee. And the list of the newly-elected
members was circulated only after much delay because it had to be
thoroughly double-checked.
