representative office in Indonesia will help them bring home remains.
</P>
<P>
The Garuda Airbus 300 on a domestic flight from Jakarta came down
on Friday afternoon during its approach to the town of Medan on the
western Indonesian island of Sumatra, possibly as a result of poor
visibility due to the thick haze from forest and brush fires
deliberately set on by Indonesian farmers which has enveloped huge
areas of Southeast Asia in a choking shroud of smog.
</P>
<P>
The flight had 222 passengers on board, including two infants and
a crew of 12. No one survived the crash, according to television
reports from Jakarta.
