<HEADLINE>
NICARAGUAN WORKERS TO HELP CONSTRUCTION OF HIGH-SPEED RAILWAY
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
Taipei,  Sept.  30  (CNA)
(By Lin Wen-fen)
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A high-ranking Taiwan labor affairs
officer confirmed on Tuesday that Nicaraguan workers will soon be
imported into Taiwan on a case-by-case basis.
</P>
<P>
Hsu Chieh-kuei, chairman of the Council of Labor Affairs (CLA),
said the Nicaraguans will most likely be employed on the high-speed
